PhillipWidgets
==============

A collection of HTML/AJAX widgets that directly bind to your database model, 
so you don't need implement database query/update in your code, it just work out of the box.

HOW TO INSTALL

* Install plugin from git:
    ./script/plugin install git://github.com/phtphan/Phillip-Widgets.git

* In your /app/controllers/application_controller.rb, add this line : 
    enable_phillip_widgets
    
    Your applcation_controller.rb should look like this:
    
      class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base
        enable_phillip_widgets
      end
    
    


HOW TO USE

* CheckBox widget:
  Ex:
    <%= phillip_checkbox("user",user.id,"active") %>
    
    => Display a checkbox that reflect the status of the current user, if unchecked it will update the active field of users table as FALSE.

* RadioButton...(coming soon)



